<p>Here’s to another 30.</p>]]></content:encoded></item><item><title><![CDATA[Minority Report]]></title><description><![CDATA[How Minority Report rightly predicted the future that we are in today!]]></description><link>http://www.sasikiran.in/minority-report/</link><guid isPermaLink="false">c05884ed-dee2-40c1-9e1f-d9ff48233556</guid><category><![CDATA[Movies]]></category><dc:creator><![CDATA[Sasi Kiran Malladi]]></dc:creator><pubDate>Wed, 01 May 2013 04:35:00 GMT</pubDate><content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>When Minority Report came in 2002, it had ultra-thin touch screens, gestures: swiping, pinch to zoom, Kinect / leap motion, Siri / Google Now like AI assistants, wearable computer gadgets like the  watch / Google Glass, self driving cars etc. Today, in 2014, we live in a world where all of that fantasized future we once had, is actually a reality.</p>

<p>I’m not really a Spielberg fan but I wonder whether he actually foresaw that the future would be something like this, or was this a purely coincidence and part of his researched script? If Spielberg did actually predict it right, well that’s really brilliant! I would want him to make Minority Report 2 as well, so that we can have a peek into our future once again. <br>
I’ve seen other sci-fi movie directors, who took way too much liberty and introduced concepts like teleportation, time travel etc. I have a feeling that these things would remain a human fantasy for a long time and may not see the light.</p>

<p>There are also movies such as <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oYziuMU2Ubs">Aditya 369</a> or the very recent <a href="http://www.imdb.com/title/tt1483013">Oblivion</a>, where after an apocalypse, the survivors would be seen wearing a silver colored pinstripe jump suit with boots! Actually, Jerry Seinfeld made <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ceRsfMaQ4r0">a joke</a> on this.</p>]]></content:encoded></item></channel></rss>